    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis happens in Neovim 0.12. I use basic `vim.lsp.buf.hover` which works as expected but only until I move the cursor and the hover window disappears (expectedly). Just between the moving of the cursor and disappearing of the window, it gets augmented by a statusline of some stardard format `[Scratch][-] ...` (this is not what I set for `statusline`).\n\nThis doesn't happen when\n\n- quitting from the focused hover window (after double `K`),\n- adding option `focusable = false` in `vim.lsp.buf.hover`.\n\nI also use floating window for diagnostics.\n\n```lua\n  vim.diagnostic.config {\n    virtual_text = false,\n    underline = true,\n    signs = true,\n    update_in_insert = false,\n    float = { border = 'rounded' }\n  }\n```\n\nSurprisingly, the statusline don't show up in this case, though this window feels to have the same implementation and is `focusable` as well.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen LSP-aware buffer and hover a term inside it. Move cursor aside. The hover window disappears with unexpected statusline showing up shortly.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe hover window disappears cleanly.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1774638290\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nsuch floating windows is implemented in Neovim only\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux, Ubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nrelease artifacts from Neovim Github release page",
